Source: worldfoundry-android-dev
Section: metapackages
Priority: optional
Maintainer: World Foundry <packages@worldfoundry.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.7.0
Homepage: https://worldfoundry.org/develop/android/
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: worldfoundry-android-dev
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 openjdk-17-jdk,
 adb,
 google-android-ndk-r26c-installer
Recommends: android-sdk-platform-tools-common
Description: Android NDK + SDK toolchain for World Foundry mobile builds
 JDK 17, adb, and the Android NDK r26c — sufficient to cross-compile
 the World Foundry engine for arm64-v8a and armeabi-v7a Android
 targets.
 .
 google-android-ndk-r26c-installer is in Ubuntu's multiverse component;
 enable it with: sudo add-apt-repository multiverse
 .
 Separate from worldfoundry-dev because Android cross-compilation
 pulls in ~3 GB of NDK that not every contributor needs.
